<author><name><![CDATA[Quietust]]></name></author>
<updated>2005-12-27T15:55:21-07:00</updated>
<published>2005-12-27T15:55:21-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=872&amp;p=7737#p7737</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=872&amp;p=7737#p7737"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Devcart: help with switch for Vertical /Horizontal mirroring]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=872&amp;p=7737#p7737"><![CDATA[
PPU A10, PPU A11, and VRAM A10 are all located at the mirroring pads. The signal which is common to BOTH sets of pads is VRAM A10 (as shown in the picture above), while the others are PPU A10 and PPU A11.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Tue Dec 27, 2005 3:55 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
