Now I'm a bit confused. I thought I would have to solder wires near the actual V / H on the chip itself (as pictured).<br /><br />I am using an SMB cart, and it only had three chips to begin with: PRG, CHR, and one 16 pin chip on the left.<br /><br />I looked for VRAM information on NESDEV / romlab, and it shows a 28 pin chip.<br /><br />Just curious where PPU A10/11 is, and the VRAM A10.<br /><br />Thanks,<br /><br />NC<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=265">No Carrier</a> — Tue Dec 27, 2005 3:45 pm</p><hr />
